name: Krapopolis

next_episode_to_air.name: Ty's Man Woman Table Chairs Food
next_episode_to_air.overview: There's this new thing called a map, and all the cool cities are on it! Tyrannis and Hippocampus start a restaurant to earn Krapopolis its spot. Stupendous follows the map to face her long time foe.

overview: In mythical ancient Greece, a flawed family of humans, gods and monsters tries to run one of the world’s first cities without killing each other.

episodes.name: All Hail the Goddess of Likeability
episodes.overview: Asskill threatens to attack Krapopolis, Tyrannis tries to use diplomacy to stop him. Deliria decides to build a temple to herself. Stupendous and Hippocampus give a trojan horse to the Asskillians.

episodes.name: The Stuperbowl
episodes.overview: Tyrannis hosts other kings for a series of games in Krapopolis where Stupendous shines. Deliria makes the games about herself. Hippocampus and Schlub track and catch the cities first serial killer.

episodes.name: Wife Swamp
episodes.overview: Tyrannis returns from a quest with a girlfriend, but it was all a setup from Deliria to make him think he's a hero. Hippocampus, Stupendous, and Schlub fight and then befriend the species of wolves.

episodes.name: Prometheus
episodes.overview: Tyrannis and Hippocampus release the only god they like, Prometheus, from his eternity on the rock, only to find he's friends with Deliria. Shlub takes Stupendous to the cyclopes island to find her dad.

episodes.name: 12 Angry Goat Herders
episodes.overview: Tyrannis creates a court system in order to absolve Shlub of a goat eating crime he didn’t commit. Hippocampus creates a sprinkler system for Killass in order to get back at Deliria.

episodes.name: Woods-Stock
episodes.overview: Tyrannis becomes the life of a party in the woods, summoning the god Dionysus. Deliria and Shlub explore their open relationship at the Parthenon.

episodes.name: Please Demeter
episodes.overview: Tyrannis begins dating the goddess Demeter and is given an option at immortality that Deliria squashes. Stupendous and Hippocampus go to Hades to retrieve Stupendous’ shield from a fallen foe.

episodes.name: Big Man on Hippocampus
episodes.overview: When Hippocampus is ostracized for his unconventional appearance, Tyrannis takes him to a science convention where he is finally appreciated for his intellect. When her friend is turned to stone, Stupendous enlists the help of Deliria who is determined to turn him back and prove she is better than Athena.

episodes.name: Dungeons and Deliria
episodes.overview: Tyrannis struggles with a ruling dilemma when a citizen is ejected from a bar for wearing newly invented pants. Meanwhile, Deliria wreaks havoc on Stupendous' secret quest, only to end up in trouble with a titan. While hunting a monster, Hippocampus ends up sparring with a tree nymph.

episodes.name: Ty's Tail Tale
episodes.overview: When Tyrannis is possessed by his deceased grandfather who rules with fear and a large scorpion tail, Shlub must fight to bring back the old Tyrannis. After Hippocampus and Stupendous bring a pregnant pegasus home, they release a range of mythical monsters to control the pegasus babies that terrorize the city.

episodes.name: Tyrdra
episodes.overview: Tyrannis invites a suicidal Hydra to come live with him and his family. Everyone grows to love her, but Tyrannis comes to regret his decision when she accidentally embroils Krapopolis in chaos.

episodes.name: Buy Low, Sell Ty
episodes.overview: With Tyrannis' support, Hippocampus overcomes his imposter syndrome and wins first prize for his invention at Hephaestus-Con, only to learn that Hephaestus selected him for his looks, not his intellect. Rebranding her image into the 'goddess of no hangovers', Deliria unintentionally starts a city-wide drunken riot while Shlub watches, afraid to confront her.

episodes.name: Contagion
episodes.overview: Tyrannis and Deliria go up north to find the dragon that is causing a plague; but when Deliria is infected with it, Ty must save his kingdom and his mom. Meanwhile, Hippo works on a cure to save the infected Krapopolis residents.

episodes.name: A Krapwork Orange
episodes.overview: Hippocampus and Stupendous train an unruly group of town-children and accidentally create an apex predator. Tyrannis mistakenly attends an Anti-Tyrannis rally.

episodes.name: Death Takes a Holiday
episodes.overview: Deliria and Tyrannis attend an exclusive island retreat hosted by the goddess Hestia. Meanwhile, back in Krapopolis, Shlub, Stupendous, and Hippocampus host a group of old-time influencers.

episodes.name: Eclipse
episodes.overview: The city of Krapopolis reckons with a solar eclipse. Tyrannis learns that it is not a cruel punishment by Zeus but a natural occurrence.

episodes.name: Salt
episodes.overview: There is a major god opening on Mt. Olympus and Deliria decide to mentor the nerdy minor god Salt for the spot as a way to spite her rival, Athena. When Krapopolis residents start moving to the wilderness to get away from the excess poop problem, Tyrannis makes it his mission to create a box that gets rid of one's number two.

episodes.name: War with the Roses
episodes.overview: Tyrannis and the nymphs arrange a meeting to negotiate peace between the city and the forest. Hippocampus and Nymph Daphne hide out in Hippocampus’ bunker and start to have fantasies of each other, which takes a turn for the worse.

episodes.name: Muse Your Illusion
episodes.overview: A plague of Muses descends upon Krapopolis. Deliria struggles to endure Shlub's centennial molting.

episodes.name: Prince Hippo
episodes.overview: When Atlanteans approach Krapopolis, Shlub reveals that Hippocampus is technically the king of Atlantis. A priestess visits Deliria and offers her services.

episodes.name: Olive Oil Crisis
episodes.overview: Deliria loses her memory when she and Stupendous transform into geese. Tyrannis tasks Shlub with procuring olive oil for Krapopolis.

episodes.name: The Tyrannis Crown Affair
episodes.overview: Tyrannis and Shlub go out to find the crown which Tyrannis lost; Deliria creates a new organization for kids.

episodes.name: Remedial Archeology
episodes.overview: Tyrannis buys a magic shell. Shlub takes Deliria to a monster wedding.

episodes.name: Ice Week!
episodes.overview: It's Ice Week in Krapopolis! Tyrannis struggles to keep his cool when he gets the hots for a visiting reporter. Shlub is paid a visit by an old friend. Hippocampus and Stupendous risk missing the festivities altogether.

episodes.name: Thor
episodes.overview: Tyrannis' little hunting mishap brings the Norse gods to Olympus. The family is forced to deal with the hunky Thor, the mischievous Loki, and some nasty bridge trolls.

episodes.name: Hades Nuts
episodes.overview: Stupendous is at it again, making trips to the underworld to visit her old fling Prack. But this time, Hades is onto her. Tyrannis tries to teach Deliria and Shlub the value of human life.

episodes.name: Mr. Boogens
episodes.overview: Garbage is piling high in Krapopolis, but the townsfolk can't wrap their heads around the concept. Tyrannis discovers how to get them in the cleaning mood. Stupendous and Hippocampus become death, the destroyer of worlds.

episodes.name: Krapocalypse
episodes.overview: Tyrannis is stuck in a time loop trying to save the city.
